post_cb({"bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_4077110_4077164_0": {"length": 25, "quality": 0.8620689655172413, "section_id": 72}}, "n3337": {"so_4077110_4077164_0": {"length": 25, "quality": 0.8620689655172413, "section_id": 67}}}, "4077164": {"PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>Short answer : Because the standard says so</p>\n<p>ISO C++03 <code>14.2/4</code></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_4077110_4077164_0\">When the name of a member template specialization appears after . or -&gt; in a postfix-expression, or after nested-name-specifier in a qualified-id, and the postfix-expression or qualified-id explicitly depends on a template-parameter (14.6.2), the member template name must be prefixed by the keyword template. <strong>Otherwise the name is assumed to name a non-template</strong>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>P.S:</p>\n<p>Without that extra use of template, the compiler does not know that the less-than token <code>(&lt;)</code> that follows is not really \"less than\" but the beginning of a template argument list.</p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2010-11-02T11:27:50.873", "Id": "4077164", "CommentCount": "1", "CreationDate": "2010-11-02T11:27:50.873", "ParentId": "4077110", "Score": "8", "OwnerUserId": "165520"}, "4077110": {"ViewCount": "805", "Body": "<p>I'm trying to find any information about template keyword used as disambiguator, but there is nothing about that. Probably I'm searching wrong keywords, but there is nothing like .template or -&gt;template in standard. Google shows only GCC problems from different forums, but not really explanation what is it used for.</p>\n<p>Code like that failed to compile without template keyword on line 11 (on GCC), but I'm not quite sure that this conforms standard.</p>\n<pre><code>template&lt;typename B&gt;\nstruct S1\n{\n    template&lt;typename T&gt; void test() {}\n};\n\ntemplate&lt;typename T&gt;\nstruct S2\n{\n    S2()\n    {\n        S1&lt;T&gt;().template test&lt;int&gt;();\n    }\n};\n\nint main()\n{\n   S2&lt;int&gt;();\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>So my question is: why does template keyword used here, what kind of ambiguity is there without that keyword and where can I read about that (I would really appreciate link to standard).</p>\n<p>Thanks.</p>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "4077164", "Title": "template disambiguator", "CreationDate": "2010-11-02T11:20:07.773", "Id": "4077110", "CommentCount": "3", "FavoriteCount": "2", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditDate": "2010-11-02T11:26:33.573", "LastEditorUserId": "475414", "LastActivityDate": "2010-11-02T11:35:06.040", "Score": "12", "OwnerUserId": "475414", "Tags": "<c++><templates><ambiguity>", "AnswerCount": "1"}});